Definition.WordDefinition: Etruscan \E*trus"can\, n. [L. Etruscus.] Of or relating to Etruria. -- n. A native or inhabitant of Etruria. [1913 Webster]
Etruscan n : a native or inhabitant of ancient Etruria; the Etruscans influenced the Romans (who had suppressed them by about 200 BC)
